  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2017 Malian Crisis Response Programme in Niger</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme has two prongs to support the overall objective: Food security: adapted farming methods, crops and seeds to increase rain fed food production while mitigating climate changes, strengthened rice production, and access to safe water and sanitation to ensure hygiene related to food preparation. Wells and family latrines will be constructed to enhance hygiene. Economic development at household level/livelihood: production groups created by refugees and host communities aiming at animal husbandry and food processing and transformation for market sale, as well as income generating activities for young people. 4% of the budget is earmarked for partner&apos;s administration costs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To contribute to food security and the development of economic revenues for greater self-sufficiency of Malian refugees and host communities in Ayorou in Niger</narrative>
  </description>
